---
/**
 * HomeEnHalls — 4 exhibition halls in English narrative
 *
 * Adapted for LagunaBeach.md from Taiwan.md's original 4-hall structure.
 * Each hall groups 2 related categories with narrative prose and article picks.
 */
import { getLangFromUrl, useTranslations } from '../../i18n/utils';

interface PickArticle {
  title: string;
  href: string;
  footnotes: number;
  readingTime: number;
  description: string;
  featured?: boolean;
}

interface Props {
  topPicks: Record<string, PickArticle[]>;
  langUrlPrefix: string;
}

const { topPicks, langUrlPrefix } = Astro.props;
const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
const t = useTranslations(lang);
---

<>
  {/* ── Hall I: The Coast ── */}
  <div class="exhibition-hall">
    <div class="hall-divider">
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
      <span class="hall-label">I — The Coast</span>
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="hall-body">
      <p>
        Seven miles of coastline, compressed between the Pacific and the San Joaquin Hills.
        Over 30 coves and beaches, each with a different character. Thousand Steps rewards
        the descent with tidepools and sea caves. Victoria Beach hides a pirate tower built
        in 1926.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/beaches`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">🏖️ The beaches</a
        >
        are not interchangeable stretches of sand — each is a pocket ecosystem shaped
        by the specific angle of its headlands.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks.beaches && topPicks.beaches.length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks.beaches.map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }

      <p>
        Below the tideline, kelp forests shelter garibaldi, sea hares, and octopus.
        The Marine Protected Area off Laguna's coast is one of the most studied in
        California. Tide pools at Crystal Cove and Shaw's Cove hold creatures most
        aquariums can't replicate.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/nature-marine-life`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">🌊 Nature & marine life</a
        >
        here is not wilderness — it's wildness within earshot of Pacific Coast Highway.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks['nature-marine-life'] && topPicks['nature-marine-life'].length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks['nature-marine-life'].map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* ── Hall II: The Story ── */}
  <div class="exhibition-hall">
    <div class="hall-divider">
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
      <span class="hall-label">II — The Story</span>
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="hall-body">
      <p>
        The Acjachemen people lived here for thousands of years. Then ranchers, then
        plein air painters who arrived in the 1900s and never left. Laguna Beach
        incorporated in 1927 specifically to prevent oil drilling. The 1993 firestorm
        destroyed 441 homes in a single afternoon.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/history`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">📜 History</a
        >
        here is not ancient — but it is fierce.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks.history && topPicks.history.length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks.history.map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }

      <p>
        The painters stayed and multiplied. The Pageant of the Masters has recreated
        classical artworks with live actors since 1933. The Sawdust Art Festival
        fills a eucalyptus grove with working studios every summer. Over 100 galleries
        line the village streets.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/art-galleries`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">🎨 Art & Galleries</a
        >
        are not ornament here — they are the reason the city exists.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks['art-galleries'] && topPicks['art-galleries'].length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks['art-galleries'].map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* ── Hall III: The Land ── */}
  <div class="exhibition-hall">
    <div class="hall-divider">
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
      <span class="hall-label">III — The Land</span>
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="hall-body">
      <p>
        Behind the beach, 22,000 acres of protected wilderness. The Top of the World
        trail gives you the entire Orange County coast in a single glance. Laguna Coast
        Wilderness Park holds California gnatcatchers, bobcats, and the last coastal
        cactus scrub in the county.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/trails`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">🥾 Trails</a
        >
        start at sea level and climb 1,000 feet in under a mile.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks.trails && topPicks.trails.length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks.trails.map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }

      <p>
        Canyon neighborhoods climb the hillsides in narrow winding roads. Top of the
        World feels like a mountain village. The Village downtown is walkable galleries
        and restaurants along PCH. South Laguna keeps an older, quieter character.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/neighborhoods`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">🏘️ Neighborhoods</a
        >
        are not subdivisions — each canyon developed its own identity.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks.neighborhoods && topPicks.neighborhoods.length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks.neighborhoods.map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* ── Hall IV: The Life ── */}
  <div class="exhibition-hall">
    <div class="hall-divider">
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
      <span class="hall-label">IV — The Life</span>
      <div class="hall-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="hall-body">
      <p>
        The Pageant of the Masters, Sawdust Art Festival, Festival of Arts — all
        running since the 1930s. First Thursdays bring the village alive monthly.
        The Fourth of July parade has been uninterrupted since 1966.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/events-festivals`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">🎭 Events & Festivals</a
        >
        are not tourism products — they grew from a community that wanted to celebrate itself.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks['events-festivals'] && topPicks['events-festivals'].length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks['events-festivals'].map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }

      <p>
        The Cliff Restaurant has served the same ocean view since 1946. Taco Loco
        has been at the same corner since 1989. Laguna's food scene is not fast-casual
        chains — it's the kind of place where the owner remembers your order.
        <a
          href={`${langUrlPrefix}/food`}
          data-ga-section="hall_pill"
          class="topic-pill">🍽️ Food</a
        >
        here is coastal California filtered through decades of local character.
      </p>
      {
        topPicks.food && topPicks.food.length > 0 && (
          <div class="hall-picks">
            {topPicks.food.map((a) => (
              <a href={a.href} data-ga-section="hall_pick" class="pick-card">
                <span class="pick-head">
                  <span class="pick-title">{a.title}</span>
                  <span class="pick-fn">{a.footnotes} sources</span>
                </span>
                {a.description && (
                  <span class="pick-desc">
                    {a.description.length > 80
                      ? a.description.slice(0, 77) + '...'
                      : a.description}
                  </span>
                )}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        )
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</>
